---
import SocialList from "@/components/SocialList.astro";
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description: "Learn about the $COWSAYS token project, creator commitment, and mission to build a sustainable Solana token ecosystem.",
	title: "About",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<section>
		<h1 class="title mb-6">About $COWSAYS</h1>
		<p class="mb-4">
			$COWSAYS is a Solana token project built around the @cowsayco community. What started as a fun Twitter bot
			sharing daily developer quotes has evolved into a transparent, community-driven token ecosystem with a
			long-term vision.
		</p>
		<p class="mb-4">
			The project combines the nostalgic charm of the classic <a class="cactus-link" href="https://github.com/tnalpgge/rank-amateur-cowsay">cowsay</a> command-line program from 1999 with modern blockchain technology, creating a sustainable token economy backed by real revenue streams.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 class="title mb-6 mt-16 text-2xl">Mission</h2>
		<p class="mb-4">
			Our mission is to build a sustainable, transparent token ecosystem that rewards the community while maintaining
			long-term value. We achieve this through:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
			<li><strong>Transparency:</strong> All financial operations, wallet balances, buyback transactions, and token burns are publicly disclosed</li>
			<li><strong>Long-term Commitment:</strong> Creator holds 20% of supply with a 10-year vesting lock, demonstrating diamond hands</li>
			<li><strong>Token Burning:</strong> All Pumpfun rewards and fees are dedicated to permanent token burning, creating a deflationary mechanism</li>
			<li><strong>Sustainable Buybacks:</strong> All profits from merchandise and NFT sales are automatically reinvested into token buybacks</li>
			<li><strong>Community Growth:</strong> Focus on building a sustainable ecosystem around the Cowsay brand</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 class="title mb-6 mt-16 text-2xl">Creator Story & Commitment</h2>
		<p class="mb-4">
			I'm the creator of the @cowsayco Twitter bot and the $COWSAYS token project. What started as a side project to
			bring daily developer humor to the community has grown into something much bigger.
		</p>
		<div class="mb-4 rounded border border-accent p-4">
			<p class="mb-2">
				<strong>My Public Commitment:</strong> I publicly commit to holding 20% of the $COWSAYS token supply (200M tokens) and will
				not sell any tokens from this allocation for a period of 10 years from the token launch date.
			</p>
			<p class="mb-2">
				<strong>Locking Mechanism:</strong> These tokens are secured with a 10-year vesting lock using <strong>Streamflow</strong> (popular & trusted platform), providing on-chain verification from day 1. This protects the floor price, stabilizes the market, and demonstrates my long-term commitment to the project.
			</p>
			<p class="text-sm text-muted">
				See <a class="cactus-link" href="https://github.com/meowso/cowsay/blob/main/TRANSPARENCY.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TRANSPARENCY.md</a> for full commitment details.
			</p>
		</div>
		<p class="mb-4">
			This commitment isn't just wordsâ€”it's backed by on-chain verification. You can verify the lock yourself on the Solana blockchain from day 1.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 class="title mb-6 mt-16 text-2xl">Token Overview</h2>
		<p class="mb-4">
			$COWSAYS is the official token of the Cowsay ecosystem, built on Solana for fast, low-cost transactions.
		</p>
		<dl class="space-y-4 mb-4">
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
				<dt>
					<span class="font-bold">Total Supply</span>
				</dt>
				<dd>1,000,000,000 (1B fixed supply)</dd>
			</div>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
				<dt>
					<span class="font-bold">Creator Allocation</span>
				</dt>
				<dd>20% (200M tokens) - 10-year vesting lock via Streamflow</dd>
			</div>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
				<dt>
					<span class="font-bold">Public Distribution</span>
				</dt>
				<dd>80% (800M tokens) - via fair bonding curve + DEX</dd>
			</div>
		</dl>
		<p class="mb-4">
			For complete tokenomics information, visit the <a class="cactus-link" href="/token/">Token page</a> or see the
			<a class="cactus-link" href="https://github.com/meowso/cowsay/blob/main/TOKENOMICS.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TOKENOMICS.md</a> file.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 class="title mb-6 mt-16 text-2xl">Key Features</h2>
		
		<h3 class="title mb-4 mt-8 text-lg">Token Burning Strategy</h3>
		<p class="mb-4">
			All rewards and fees from Pump.fun are dedicated to <strong>permanent token burning</strong>:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
			<li><strong>Pumpfun Trading Fees:</strong> Portion of trading fees distributed back to creator</li>
			<li><strong>Pumpfun Rewards:</strong> Any rewards, incentives, or fee rebates from Pump.fun platform</li>
			<li><strong>Burning Process:</strong> Funds are used to purchase tokens from the market and permanently burn them</li>
			<li><strong>Supply Reduction:</strong> Creates a deflationary mechanism that reduces circulating supply over time</li>
		</p>
		<p class="mb-4">
			This deflationary mechanism works alongside our buyback program to create a sustainable tokenomics model.
		</p>

		<h3 class="title mb-4 mt-8 text-lg">Automated Buyback Mechanism</h3>
		<p class="mb-4">
			All profits from the following Cowsay ecosystem sources are automatically reinvested into $COWSAYS token buybacks:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
			<li><strong>Merchandise Shop:</strong> All profits from T-shirts, mugs, mousepads, and other products</li>
			<li><strong>NFT Auctions:</strong> All proceeds from auctioned quote artwork NFTs</li>
			<li><strong>Future Revenue:</strong> Any additional revenue generated by the Cowsay ecosystem</li>
		</ul>
		<p class="mb-4">
			<strong>Note:</strong> Pumpfun rewards and fees are handled separately through token burning (see above), not through buybacks.
		</p>
		<p class="mb-4">
			This creates a sustainable buyback mechanism where the success of the Cowsay brand directly benefits token
			holders through continuous buybacks for 10 years.
		</p>

		<h3 class="title mb-4 mt-8 text-lg">Full Transparency</h3>
		<p class="mb-4">
			We believe in complete transparency. All financial operations are publicly tracked:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
			<li>Real-time wallet balance tracking</li>
			<li>Profit & Loss dashboard</li>
			<li>On-chain buyback transaction history</li>
			<li>On-chain token burn transaction history</li>
			<li>Public wallet addresses</li>
		</ul>
		<p class="mb-4">
			Visit the <a class="cactus-link" href="/transparency/">Transparency Dashboard</a> to see everything in real-time.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 class="title mb-6 mt-16 text-2xl">Resources & Links</h2>
		
		<ul class="space-y-2 mb-4">
			<li>
				<a class="cactus-link" href="/token/">Token Information</a> - Complete token details and buyback tracker
			</li>
			<li>
				<a class="cactus-link" href="/transparency/">Transparency Dashboard</a> - Financial transparency and wallet tracking
			</li>
			<li>
				<a class="cactus-link" href="/shop/">Merchandise Shop</a> - Support the project and contribute to buybacks
			</li>
			<li>
				<a class="cactus-link" href="/nfts/">NFT Auctions</a> - Collect unique quote artwork NFTs
			</li>
			<li>
				<a class="cactus-link" href="https://github.com/meowso/cowsay/blob/main/TOKENOMICS.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Full Tokenomics</a> - Detailed tokenomics documentation
			</li>
			<li>
				<a class="cactus-link" href="https://github.com/meowso/cowsay/blob/main/TRANSPARENCY.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Transparency & Commitment</a> - Complete transparency statement
			</li>
			<li>
				<a class="cactus-link" href="https://twitter.com/cowsayco" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@cowsayco on Twitter</a> - Follow for daily developer quotes
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2 class="title mb-6 mt-16 text-2xl">Connect</h2>
		<SocialList />
	</section>
</PageLayout>
